# 1. Indls Excel-filen (frste ark)
BI <- read_excel("BI.xlsx")
# 2. Omform til langt format (forudstter at frste kolonne hedder 'rstal')
BI_long <- BI %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = -Branche,
               names_to = "r",
               values_to = "Bruttoindkomst")
ggplot(BI_long, aes(x = r, y = Bruttoindkomst, color = Branche, group = Branche)) +
  geom_line() +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::comma) + 
  labs(title = "Bruttoindkomst pr. Branche over tid",
       x = "r",
       y = "Belb (i mio. kr.)") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30, hjust = 1, size = 10)  # mindre vinkel og strre skrift
  ) +
  scale_x_discrete(breaks = unique(BI_long$r)[seq(1, length(unique(BI_long$r)), by = 5)])  # viser fx hvert 4. r

  mutate(r_num = as.integer(substr(r, 1, 4)))

# Lav animation

  geom_line(linewidth = 1.2) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::comma) + 
  labs(title = "Bruttoindkomst pr. Branche: {frame_along}",

       y = "Belb (i mio. kr.)") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30, hjust = 1, size = 10)
  ) +
  transition_reveal(r_num)

library(tidyverse)

# Indls og forbered data
BNP_BVT <- read_csv("BNP_BVT_andel.csv") %>%
  mutate(BNP_mio = BNP_mia * 1000)
## Rows: 59 Columns: 5
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: ","
## dbl (5): r, BNP_mia, BVT_mio, BNP_mio, Andel
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
# Filtrer: fjern rkker hvor BVT mangler
BNP_BVT_start <- BNP_BVT %>%
  filter(!is.na(BVT_mio))

# Definr frste flles r som basis
base_BNP <- BNP_BVT_start$BNP_mio[1]
base_BVT <- BNP_BVT_start$BVT_mio[1]

# Beregn indeks fra frste flles r
BNP_BVT_indeks <- BNP_BVT_start %>%
  mutate(
    BNP_index = (BNP_mio / base_BNP) * 100,
    BVT_index = (BVT_mio / base_BVT) * 100
  ) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(BNP_index, BVT_index), names_to = "Variabel", values_to = "Indeks")

# Tegn graf
ggplot(BNP_BVT_indeks, aes(x = r, y = Indeks, color = Variabel)) +
  geom_line(linewidth = 1.2) +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  scale_y_continuous(
    labels = scales::label_number(suffix = " %"),
    limits = c(0, 500)  # eller hjere, alt efter hvor stor vkst BVT har
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "Procentuel udvikling i BNP og landbrugets BVT  fra frste flles r",
    x = "r",
    y = "Indeks (startr = 100)",
    color = NULL
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30, hjust = 1))

# Divider indeks med 100 s det bliver rigtige procenttal
BNP_BVT_indeks_plot <- BNP_BVT_indeks %>%
  mutate(Indeks = Indeks / 100)

# Tegn graf
ggplot(BNP_BVT_indeks_plot, aes(x = r, y = Indeks, color = Variabel)) +
  geom_line(linewidth = 1.2) +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  scale_y_continuous(
    labels = scales::label_percent(accuracy = 1),
    limits = c(0, max(BNP_BVT_indeks_plot$Indeks) * 1.05),
    breaks = seq(0, max(BNP_BVT_indeks_plot$Indeks), by = 0.25)  # fx hvert 25 %
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(
    breaks = seq(min(BNP_BVT_indeks_plot$r), max(BNP_BVT_indeks_plot$r), by = 2)
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "Procentuel udvikling i BNP og landbrugets BVT  fra frste flles r",
    x = "r",
    y = "Procentvis vkst siden startr",
    color = NULL
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30, hjust = 1))
